==English==
===Noun===
'''backpack''' (''plural'' '''backpacks''')
#A [[knapsack]], sometimes [[mount]]ed on a light [[frame]], but always supported by [[strap]]s, worn on a person's back when [[hike|hiking]].
#A similarly placed item containing a [[parachute]] or other [[life-support]]  [[equipment]].

====Translations====
{{top}}
*Danish: [[rygsæk]] (1)
*Finnish: [[reppu]] (1), [[selkäreppu]] (1)
{{mid}}
*French: [[sac à dos]] (1)
*Norwegian: [[ryggsekk]] (1)
{{bottom}}
====Synonyms====
* [[knapsack]] (''US'')
* [[rucksack]]

===Intransitive verb===
'''to backpack'''
#To hike and camp overnight in backcountry with one's gear carried in a backpack.
#To engage in low-cost, generally urban, travel with minimal luggage and frugal accommodations.

===Transitive verb===
'''to backpack'''
#To place or carry (an item or items) in a backpack.

====Derived terms====
*[[backpacker]]
*[[backpacking]]<!--noun-->

